WebSocket Activity Stream Implementation - Complete

Changes made to /app/nextjs-project/app/page.tsx:

1. Replaced static ACTIVITY_STEPS array with dynamic AGENT_NAME_MAP and WS_METRICS_BASE constants
2. Added ActivityEvent interface for typed WebSocket events
3. Rewrote ActivityStream component to render real-time events with LIVE/CONNECTING badge
4. Replaced timer-based simulation with real WebSocket connection:
   - Fetches API key from /api/lyzr-config
   - Connects to wss://metrics.studio.lyzr.ai/ws/{session_id}?x-api-key={key}
   - Parses incoming messages and maps to agent names via resolveAgentName()
   - Falls back to simulated stream if WebSocket unavailable
5. Updated handleGenerate() to generate shared session_id, start WebSocket before API call
6. Updated handleNewCampaign() to clear activity events
7. Updated ActivityStream JSX usage with new props (events, wsConnected)
8. Added cleanup for WebSocket on component unmount

All constraints maintained:
- react-icons/fi only (no lucide-react, no emojis)
- No toast/sonner
- No sign-in/OAuth
- Uses aiAgent.ts for AI integrations
